    title: "Configuring Automatic Reorder Points",
    description: "Set reorder levels so AskBiz alerts you or generates purchase orders when stock runs low.",
    topic: "Advanced Inventory",
    topicSlug: "inventory-advanced",
    readTime: 3,
    content: [
      { heading: "What is a reorder point?", body: "A reorder point is the stock level at which you should place a new order to avoid running out. It accounts for lead time — how long your supplier takes to deliver — and your average daily sales rate. If you sell 10 units per day and your supplier delivers in 5 days, your reorder point is at least 50 units. AskBiz calculates this automatically based on your historical data." },
      { heading: "Setting reorder levels", body: "Go to Inventory > Reorder Settings. For each product, you can set the reorder point manually or let AskBiz calculate it from your sales velocity and supplier lead time. Set the reorder quantity — how much to order when triggered. You can also set a safety stock buffer to account for demand spikes or delivery delays." },
      { heading: "Reorder alerts", body: "When stock falls below the reorder point, AskBiz sends an alert. The alert appears in your Daily Brief, on the Inventory Dashboard, and as a push notification if configured. The alert includes the product name, current stock, reorder point, suggested order quantity, and the preferred supplier." },
      { heading: "Auto-generated purchase orders", body: "Enable auto-PO in Reorder Settings to have AskBiz create draft purchase orders automatically when stock hits the reorder point. The draft PO includes the product, quantity, and preferred supplier. Review and submit it — or let it auto-submit if you trust the calculation. This closes the loop from detection to action without manual intervention." },
    ],
    faq: [
      { q: "Can AskBiz calculate reorder points automatically?", a: "Yes. Enable Auto-Calculate in Reorder Settings. AskBiz uses your average daily sales rate and supplier lead time to set the point." },
      { q: "What if I have multiple suppliers for one product?", a: "Set a preferred supplier for auto-PO generation. You can change the supplier on the draft PO before submitting." },
    ],
    related: ["pos-low-stock-alert-config", "pos-purchase-orders", "pos-batch-expiry-tracking"],
    keywords: ["reorder", "auto-order", "stock levels", "inventory", "purchasing"],
